        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-07-28 18:25:02.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI was listening to the recorded session that referenced this gerri patchset. It appears to me that this \"dot\" file defines \"what is expected\". Is that accurate? If so, how do we compare \"expected\" to actual or even capture actual as code is developed and committed?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "5874384d55772dd2d3cd9653b5ee165109c0a3e8",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 1675,
          "name": "David Bainbridge",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "dbainbri@ciena.com",
          "username": "dbainbri"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-07-28 18:28:49.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nIf we want to ensure all dependencies are documented, don't we need to formalize how dependencies are specified (i.e. in a file in each project as opposed to a wiki?) and then a security mechanism so that only defined dependencies can be invoked, so that one module cannot call another until a dependencies is officially defined?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
      {
        "id": "9b36cda7032a7c65ff032319ffe57d43af67394a",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 219,
          "name": "Gildas Lanilis",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "gildaslanilis@gmail.com",
          "username": "glanilis"
        },
        "author_role": "OWNER",
        "timestamp": "2017-07-31 15:53:01.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nThe dot file summarizes the API dependencies has it was defined in project's Release plan. The dot file is not what I or someone else is expecting. For more details, https://wiki.onap.org/download/attachments/8231717/ONAP%20API%20DependenciesV1.pdf?api=v2\n\nTo formalize the API, for the M3 API Freeze milestone, the Architecture Committee will ensure all dependencies have been defined.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
